{"type":"message","id":"31733da5","parentId":"6275613d","timestamp":"2026-02-25T06:38:40.810Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, the user wants to separate the workspaces so they're not sharing. But the original workspace files are shared (MEMORY.md, etc.). If we copy them to each agent's workspace, they'll have their own copies that can diverge.\n\nActually, looking more carefully at the user's request - they want the agents to have separate workspaces. The question is: should MEMORY.md (the trading ledger) be:\n1. Shared (both agents see the same trades)\n2. Separate (each has their own copy)\n\nGiven that MEMORY.md is the trading ledger and stock agent needs to read it, probably option 1 makes more sense - keep MEMORY.md in a shared location, or have stock agent reference the workspace location.\n\nActually, let me reconsider. The user said \"将2个agent的workspace分开\" - separate the 2 agents' workspaces. This means each agent should have their own workspace directory.\n\nBut MEMORY.md contains the trading records which both agents need. If we separate:\n- Main agent workspace: general assistant files\n- Stock agent workspace: stock-specific files, but needs to reference trading records\n\nI think the cleanest approach is:\n1. Main agent gets `/Users/hope/.openclaw/agents/main/workspace/` (copy of current shared files)\n2. Stock agent keeps `/Users/hope/.openclaw/agents/stock/workspace/` (already exists, needs cleanup)\n3. stock agent's config points to stock/workspace\n\n\n4. I need to copy the essential trading records to the stock agent's workspace or establish a shared reference so it can access the trading ledger.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"functions.exec:63","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cp ~/.openclaw/workspace/MEMORY.md ~/.openclaw/workspace/SOUL.md ~/.openclaw/workspace/AGENTS.md ~/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md ~/.openclaw/workspace/USER.md ~/.openclaw/agents/main/workspac